entries.context: A natural language name identifying the code system. This name should be usable as an identifier for the module by machine processing applications such as code generation.
A short, descriptive, user-friendly title for the code system.
The name of the organization or individual that published the code system.
The name of an individual to contact.
A free text natural language description of the code system from a consumer's perspective.
entries.source: Role kontaktní osoby. FHIR Code system definition for HL7 v2 table 0131 (Contact Role).

entries.context: A representation of the meaning of the code in the system, following the rules of the system.
A description of the property- why it is defined, and how its value might be used.
A human readable string that is the recommended default way to present this concept to a user.

The formal definition of the concept. The code system resource does not make formal definitions required, because of the prevalence of legacy systems. However, they are highly recommended, as without them there is no formal meaning associated with the concept.
